The paper deals with the statistical characterization of the signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) in cellular networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines. However, based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of communication systems. The paper also mentions the modeling of wireless communication scenarios, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The mention of stochastic geometry modeling and analysis points towards cs.SY (Systems and Control), while the discussion of coverage, achievable rate, and bit error probability (BEP) suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.PF (Performance).
